  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\n(Split off from #4327.)\r\n\r\nIn the [`Environment.develop` function](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/environment/environment.js#L73), you can see that `config.networks[network]` is overwritten with a custom, barebones, network config.  Presumably, the new network config should keep other existing config options in place, and only overwrite `network_id`, `provider`, and other ways of specifying a provider; leaving in place such things as `gas`, `disableConfirmationListener`, etc.\r\n\r\nThis prevents configuring the network used in `truffle develop`.  It also prevents configuring the network used in `truffle test`, although solving that will also require addressing #4327.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.12",
